Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi Hires Citadel’s Arturo De Pena as Loan Sales Head

-- B y   K r i s t e n   H a u n s s
-- 
2011-12-06T17:26:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/bank-of-tokyo-mitsubishi-hires-citadel-s-arturo-de-pena-as-loan-sales-head.html
The  Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd. 
hired Arturo de Pena as head of loan sales and trading in the
syndicated loan capital markets group.  He reports to Chris O’Neill, BTMU’s group head of
syndications in the investment banking division for the
Americas, which is headed by general manager Taiju Hisai,
according to a statement distributed by  Business Wire  yesterday.  “Art’s client focus, broad experience and strategic
thinking will contribute greatly to the continued growth of our
syndications franchise,” O’Neill said in the statement.  De Pena previously worked at Citadel LLC’s securities unit.
Before that he worked at the Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc
where he was head of loan sales and trading for the Americas,
according to the release.  De Pena didn’t immediately return a telephone call to his
cell phone seeking comment. O’Neill also didn’t immediately
return a telephone call.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kristen Haunss in New York at 
